    "decisions": {
      "module_01": {
        "choice": "A",
        "reasoning": "The current system consists of a single backend service, so a single-app repository keeps the setup simple and easy to manage. Introducing a monorepo at this stage would add unnecessary complexity without clear benefits. As the system evolves into multiple services, it can be refactored into a monorepo if needed.",
        "module": 1,
        "recorded_at": "2026-04-28T08:54:47.470Z"
      },
      "module_02": {
        "choice": "A",
        "reasoning": "The system primarily performs fast lookups of short_code to original_url, which benefits from indexing and strong consistency. PostgreSQL provides reliable uniqueness constraints, durability, and supports future analytics queries, making it a better fit than a document database for this use case.",
        "module": 2,
        "recorded_at": "2026-04-28T10:18:03.395Z"
      },
      "module_03": {
        "choice": "A",
        "reasoning": "I chose /r/<code> because it keeps public redirect routes separate from application routes like /health, /ready, /login, /admin, and /api. The extra prefix is a small cost for safer growth, fewer route collisions, and clearer separation between admin/product endpoints and redirect behavior.",
        "module": 3,
        "recorded_at": "2026-04-29T16:53:20.950Z"
      },
      "module_04": {
        "choice": "A",
        "reasoning": "This URL shortener is still closer to an internal admin-protected API than a full user-facing login system. Right now, we mainly need to protect write endpoints like POST /shorten and delete/manage endpoints from abuse. We do not need full logout, sessions, or user identity flows yet, so JWT would add extra complexity before it is needed. An API key is easier to build, test, and rate-limit safely at this stage: every protected request must include the key, and the server can reject requests without it. Later, if the project grows into a real multi-user dashboard, JWT can be added then.",
        "module": 4,
        "recorded_at": "2026-04-30T08:37:31.697Z"
      }
    },
